&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; With amazing calm Tucson just simply walks by them and ignores their taunts.
&gt;  He had a feeling he was expected to lash out in draconic rage which would
&gt; cloud his train of thought, thus making him more vulnerable to failure.
&gt; Instead, he stumbles upon a discarded bone, rather thick in size and simply
&gt; snaps it with a whip of the tip of his tail, swiping it away and shattering
&gt; it into a thousand bone fragments.  He then simply shrugs with his front
&gt; haunches.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; Excuse me, but that bone was in my way. &quot;

&lt;NEW&gt;

The hooting and catcalling continued as TUSCON was led down the
walkways, if anyone noticed the bone breaking manuver, there was no
visible or audial sign of it.

As TUSCON moved he could see that there were aliens of different
types, but also machine life forms as well. And it was towards these
that he was led, a large door parting to let them in. The guards that
let them in carefully kept their weapons on the ready as they passed
through.

GUILEDART stopped as he opened the last gate and gestured to TUSCON,
&quot;This is where you will stay as you prepare for your battles.&quot; He
pointed for him to go inside. &quot;Your . . . &quot; He paused as if looking
for the proper word and then finally found one. &quot; . . . your trainer
will be inside.&quot;

Approaching the gate from the other side was a large and imposing
figure of seemingly massive proportions. A few inches shorter than
TUSCON himself he was thick at the shoulders and hips, huge horns of
some type jutting out.

It was the Maximal known as BIG CONVOY!

A CONVOY!?!? The Convoy ranks higher than a Prime but less than a
Magnus. There are very few Convoys, and they are considered to be flag
rank and are typically used to assist the Magnus in his duties.

But what was BIG doing out here? Could this be one of the &#39;other&#39;
reasons that LEO PRIME is out here, to look for BIG CONVOY, he was
rumored to be a close friend of LIO CONVOY.

&quot;Another one.&quot; He grumbled under his breath as he looked at TUSCON.

